Precitec.Filter.Intersect2Lines.Beschrei.Text: Find the point of intersection of two straight lines. Input: 1) Input ROI (for context and optionally for checking validity). 2) First line (as provided by the filter EstimateLine or LineFit) 3) Second line (as provided by the filter EstimateLine or LineFit). Output: 1) Intersection valid (1,0). An intersection can't be found if the lines are parallel, coincident, or any input is invalid. The intersection is not valid if the option "Intersection point inside ROI" and the intersection point is outside the input ROI 2-3) X and Y coordinate of the intersection. The output coordinates are expressed in relationship to the input image 4) Angle between lines (degrees, 0 - 180).

Precitec.Filter.ContextNormalizeDouble.B.Text: Filter to transform the context of the inputs, maintaining the same position and changing the numerical value accordingly. The first input pipe provides the reference context, that will be used for the output. The meaning of the second and third input can be chosen among: x coordinate (will be affected by the x component of the context) , y coordinate (will be affected by the y component of the context), pure number (in this case, the numerical value will not be affected by context), width and height (both affected only by the sampling factor). In the default case, the inputs are considered to be an x coordinate and a y coordinate.
